SIMPLE: concupiscible
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Concupiscible
<hw>Con*cu`pis*ci*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>concupiscible</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Exciting to, or liable
to be affected by, concupiscence; provoking lustful desires.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Exciting desire, good or evil.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The schools reduce all the passions to these two heads, the
<qex>concupiscible</qex> and irascible appetite.</q>
<rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Concupiscibleness</ent>⟦br⟧
